      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(model-fallback): don't rethrow provider-side AbortErrors as user cancellations",
        "body": "## Problem\n\nWhen the LLM API closes the connection mid-stream, the fetch layer surfaces `AbortError(\"This operation was aborted\")` with **no external abort signal triggered** (`\"externalAbort: false\"` in trajectory). The existing guard `shouldRethrowAbort()` returned `false` for these errors (because `isTimeoutError` matched the \"operation was aborted\" message), so they fell through to the fallback loop but were never retried — the error propagated up and produced `SILENT_REPLY_TOKEN` in group/channel sessions, permanently silencing the topic.\n\n**Reproduction path (source inspection + confirmed by real trajectory):**\n\n1. Provider drops connection → `AbortError(\"This operation was aborted\")`, `\"promptErrorSource: \"prompt\"`, `\"externalAbort: false\"`\n2. `runFallbackCandidate`: `shouldRethrowAbort` = false (isTimeoutError matches) → error not rethrown, not retried → `return { ok: false, error }`\n3. `agent-runner-execution.ts` catch: `isGenericRunnerFailure: true`\n4. `resolveExternalRunFailureTextForConversation`: group/channel session + generic failure → `SILENT_REPLY_TOKEN`\n5. User receives **zero visible response**; every subsequent message in the same topic repeats the same path → topic is permanently silenced\n\n## Fix\n\nReplace the guard in `runFallbackCandidate` with a direct check: only rethrow `AbortError` when the external abort signal is actually set (user/gateway cancellation). Provider-side `AbortError`s without an external signal now fall through to the next fallback candidate.\n\n```typescript\n// Before:\nif (shouldRethrowAbort(err) && !normalizedFailover) {\n  throw err;\n}\n\n// After:\nif (isFallbackAbortError(err) && !params.abortSignal?.aborted && !normalizedFailover) {\n  throw err;\n}\n```\n\nThis also removes the unused `shouldRethrowAbort` helper and `isTimeoutError` import.\n\n## Scope\n\n- **2 files changed**, +31 / -6\n- `model-fallback.ts`: guard condition change (core fix)\n- `model-fallback.test.ts`: updated existing user-abort test + added provider-side abort regression test\n\n## What this does NOT change\n\n- `agent-runner-execution.ts` failure routing (SILENT_REPLY_TOKEN for generic group failures) — this is a separate concern that can be addressed in a follow-up if needed\n- `compact.ts` abort signal forwarding\n- No config, plugin, or gateway protocol changes\n\n## Before-fix behavior proof (redacted)\n\nTwo trajectory records from the affected installation:\n\n**Event 1 — 2026-06-06T02:14:27Z**\n```json\n{ \"type\": \"trace.artifacts\", \"provider\": \"<provider>\", \"data\": { \"finalStatus\": \"error\", \"aborted\": true, \"externalAbort\": false, \"promptError\": \"This operation was aborted\", \"promptErrorSource\": \"prompt\" } }\n```\n\n**Event 2 — 2026-06-06T09:02:28Z** (same session — confirms repeat-silence pattern)\n```json\n{ \"type\": \"trace.artifacts\", \"provider\": \"<provider>\", \"data\": { \"finalStatus\": \"error\", \"aborted\": true, \"externalAbort\": false, \"promptError\": \"This operation was aborted\", \"promptErrorSource\": \"prompt\" } }\n```\n\nBoth: `externalAbort: false` → no external signal fired → `dispatch complete replies=0` in gateway logs.\n\n## Tests\n\n78/78 model-fallback tests pass. New regression test `\"falls back when AbortError comes from the LLM provider (no external signal)\"` verifies that provider-side AbortError enters the fallback chain instead of being rethrown.",
        "branch": "fix/abort-no-visible-reply-fallback",
        "head_sha": "957d76b1a7c5963d34b55c9efbe4d737c305d679",
